cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY

This paper proposes a new video coding method based on compressive sampling, which involves measuring and reconstructing video data using fewer samples than traditional methods. This technique is commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also discusses the use of total variation (TV) minimization, which is a popular method in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.NI). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of this method in mobile broadcast (cs.SY).
